This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with contour detection using convolutional neural networks. The use of deep learning models and attention mechanisms also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the use of Conditional Random Fields (CRFs) and the evaluation on publicly available datasets suggest that it could also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.NE) and Multimedia (cs.MM) categories.
